SQS messages

messages in SQS queues will continue to exist after the EC2 instance has been processed - until the message is deleted

the message must be deleted after processing the to prevent the message from received and processed again once visibility timeout expires

Distributed messaging systems:
 - the components of your distributed system (EC2 instances)
 - the queue (SQS)
 - mesages in the queue
 
a system wuth several components send messages that are stored across multiple SQS servers

 - message sent to a queue, distributed across SQS servers redundantly
 - when the second component is ready to process a mesagfe it consumes it from the queue, that first message is returned
 while it is being processed, it remains in the queue and not returned to subsequent receive requests for visibility timeout
 - second component deletes message A to prevent message from being received and processed again once visibility itmeout
 
 long polling helps reduce the cost of SQS by eliminating number of emoty resources and false empty responses (messages sent twice is unlikely))
 
